{
  "texts": [
    "Once a diameter of 90° was reached, the diameter remained constant.",
    "The second type of stimulus sequence was a fictive female varying her size, position, and rotation.",
    "The fictive female was generated in the same manner as that for the input of the 1-to-1 network (see 'Visual input reconstruction').",
    "We took the angular size of the fictive female (65 visual degrees for a size of 1.0, where the female faces away from the male at the centre of the image) and used it to set the angular size of the fictive female on the projection screen.",
    "We considered three kinds of fictive female stimulus sequences with 9 different sequences in total (Supplementary Video 1 and Extended Data Fig. 8); we first describe them at a high level and then separately in more detail."
  ]
}